FBIS4-30406 "dreas123__a94010" FBIS-EAS-94-123-A Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 ANNEX Japan LDP's Watanabe Urges Conservative Alliance LDP's Watanabe Urges Conservative Alliance OW2606131394 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 26 Jun 94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2606131394 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] Asked how the next government should be created, Watanabe, former deputy prime minister and foreign minister, of the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP], in an interview with reporters at the Diet building on 25 June, stressed the need to create a "conservatives-conservatives alliance" -- composed of such conservative forces as Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party] and the LDP -- saying: "I hope a stable government will be formed with those who share the same views. Even if the right and left wingers get together, they will agree with the plan in principle but oppose it in practice. What we need are tolerate minds to iron out minor difference of opinions for the best common interests."
